<Layout
  title="How to Build a Mobile App for Your Bold Commerce Website"
  description="Converting your Bold Commerce website into mobile apps is a great way to boost engagement, retention, and drive long-term revenue. Read on to learn the best way to do it."
>
  <Nav />

  <section class="py-20 md:py-32 px-4">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Website Builders</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-6">How to Build a Mobile App for Your Bold Commerce Website</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8">Converting your Bold Commerce website into mobile apps is a great way to boost engagement, retention, and drive long-term revenue. Read on to learn the best way to do it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-slate">
      <p id="">MobiLoud is built to convert any website into native mobile apps. It's perfect for <a href="https://boldcommerce.com/" id="">Bold Commerce</a> sites, and allows you to launch your mobile app in less than a month, with minimal overhead, without sacrificing key features from your website.</p><p id="">In this article, we'll walk you through the process of converting your Bold Commerce website into a mobile app with MobiLoud, compared to the traditional mobile app development methods.</p><p id="">Keep reading to learn more!</p><blockquote id="">MobiLoud lets you convert your website into high-quality mobile apps, for minimal investment and effort, and with virtually no overhead.&nbsp;And it's risk-free! <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id="">Book a free demo now</a> to see how we can help you take your business to the next level.</blockquote><h2 id="">Why You Should Build a Mobile App for Your Bold Commerce Website</h2><p id="">Let’s get straight to the point: mobile apps offer an experience that a website just can’t match, no matter how optimized your site is for mobile browsers.&nbsp;</p><p id="">Mobile internet usage continues to rise. <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/mobile-apps-vs-mobile-websites" id="">90% of mobile users’ time is spent in apps</a> and studies show that mobile internet traffic accounts for approximately <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/what-percentage-of-internet-traffic-is-mobile" id="">57% of all internet traffic</a>. People are clearly spending more time on mobile apps than mobile websites.</p><p id="">On the eCommerce side, smartphones alone generated around <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/568684/e-commerce-website-visit-and-orders-by-device/" id="">77% of retail site traffic</a> globally, responsible for generating two-thirds of online shopping orders during the first quarter of 2024. Mobile eCommerce sales reached $2.2 trillion and made up about <a href="https://www.statista.com/chart/13139/estimated-worldwide-mobile-e-commerce-sales/" id="">60% of all eCommerce sales around the world</a> in 2023. It is even expected to grow even bigger in 2027.</p><figure id="" class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:1024px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="1024px"><div id=""><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/68d4c343238f5ca554391c31_68d4c33b3f0953ab768130b4_metric%2520image%25201.webp" width="auto" height="auto" alt="" loading="auto" id=""></div></figure><p id="">‍</p><p id="">Conversion rates, engagement and key metrics are also higher across the board for mobile apps vs mobile websites. Here are some of the key figures:</p><ul id=""><li id="">Users view 4.2x more products per session on mobile apps vs mobile sites.</li><li id="">Conversion rates on apps are 3x higher than mobile websites.</li><li id="">Entertainment apps convert 233% higher than mobile web in the same industry.</li><li id="">Travel apps convert 220% higher.</li><li id="">Retail apps convert 94% higher.</li><li id="">On-demand apps convert 307% higher.</li><li id="">Overall, apps average 157% higher conversion rates than mobile websites.</li></ul><p id="">These statistics clearly show that if you do not have a mobile app for your business, you’re probably missing out on a large chunk of potential customers.</p><p id="">Mobile apps offer massive benefits to businesses and at this point in time, having a mobile app is a must. Take a look at the key mobile app benefits for businesses:</p><h3 id="">A better mobile shopping experience</h3><p id="">Your customers will have a better time shopping on mobile than on your mobile website. Your store will be easier to navigate, with fewer of the annoyances and distractions you get when shopping on a mobile website. A mobile app allows them to shop anywhere and anytime.</p><h3 id="">Increased loyalty and retention</h3><p id="">The better user experience directly correlates to increased loyalty and retention. If people love shopping with you, they'll come back and do it again.</p><p id="">Apps are tailor-made for fostering loyalty and increasing retention rates. They make it easy for people to get in, with just one tap from their home screen. And that home screen icon is a constant reminder of your brand, a permanent fixture in your customers' headspace.</p><p id="">This is all going to translate to a higher lifetime value from every one of your app users.</p><h3 id="">An owned sales channel</h3><p id="">Worried about a dip in Google SEO rankings, or the constant cost of driving traffic from paid ads?</p><p id="">An app gives you an owned channel, not susceptible to the platform risk of Google, Facebook, or online marketplaces.</p><p id="">You can reach out directly to your customers through push notifications, and re-engage your customers, even if your reach on external platforms is diminished for whatever reason.</p><h3 id="">App store presence</h3><p id="">Finally, getting into the app stores is a powerful thing.</p><p id="">They can provide a new acquisition channel. They also provide a ton of social proof. When someone sees you have a mobile app in the iOS App Store or Google Play Store, your brand instantly looks more legitimate and trustworthy.</p><p id="">Now let’s look at a comparison between MobiLoud and other ways to build mobile apps.</p><h2 id="">How to Build a Mobile App for Your Bold Commerce Website</h2><p id="">If speed, cost-efficiency, and maintaining your existing site’s functionality are top priorities, <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id="">MobiLoud</a> offers a solid solution to <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/how-to-create-an-app" id="">build a mobile app</a> out of your website.</p><p id="">Our platform allows you to convert your existing website into a fully functional mobile app for both iOS and Android, without the need to rebuild everything from scratch. </p><p id="">This method leverages the responsive design of your website, packaging it into a native app that can be distributed via the app stores. It supports native features like push notifications, offline functionality, and in-app purchases, providing a smooth mobile experience for your users. </p><p id="">Since you’re not starting from scratch, this approach saves time and money, making it a smart choice for businesses that want to go mobile without the high costs of custom development.</p><p id="">If you’re a big brand with a ton of resources at your disposal, you might be able to afford rebuilding from scratch using these options:<br><br><strong id="">Custom Native Development</strong>: This is the most customizable option, where you build separate apps for iOS and Android (which doubles the development time and cost). While this offers full control, it’s also expensive and time-consuming, requiring a dedicated team of developers to create and maintain the app.&nbsp;</p><p id=""><strong id="">Cross-Platform Development</strong>: Frameworks like React Native or Flutter allow you to build a single codebase that works across both platforms. This is faster and more affordable than custom development but still requires a substantial level of coding expertise and cost as you will still need to hire a team of developers to create and maintain the app for you.</p><p id=""><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/how-much-does-it-cost-to-create-an-app" id="">Mobile app development costs a lot</a>, and adds a lot of ongoing work, which comes with significant overhead expenses. Keep in mind that the right choice depends on your business's specific needs, budget, and timeline. So, which option would you pick?</p><h2 id="">Convert Your Bold Commerce Website To A Mobile App With MobiLoud Today</h2><p id=""><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id="">MobiLoud</a> lets you skip the pain and high cost of mobile app development. Our platform can turn any website into native mobile apps. It’s a done-for-you service that has the best elements of a no code app builder and custom app development.</p><p id="">With MobiLoud, you can launch apps with zero coding and zero technical ability. There’s no need to hire and manage developers, and you won’t even have to spend money close to the level of investment needed to build fully custom apps from the ground up.</p><p id="">Our solution doesn’t limit you to blocks and templates. It fully converts your existing website into apps, which are fully synced with your site to make the apps simple to update and maintain.</p><p id="">You can ship a <em id="">full-featured mobile app</em> that carries over all the features of your website, and feels like a fully custom native app to the end user, for minimal cost, done in less than a month.</p><figure id="" class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id=""><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f376e06e08bf7d6a29_20250702T0913-cc627ec2-99cc-46f6-81fd-923171fb4f1b.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id=""></div><figcaption id="">A few apps we've built at MobiLoud - check out more examples <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/examples" id="">here</a></figcaption></figure><h3 id="">How It Works</h3><p id="">With MobiLoud, your app will be a full, live reflection of your website. We strip away the browser tabs, and add a few small native mobile touches, such as navigation UI, a tab menu and splash screens. We then put together native code to allow your app to run in Android and iOS operating systems, and let you send native mobile push notifications.</p><p id="">Our approach has a number of advantages:</p><ul id=""><li id="">It lets you quickly and easily go to market with an app, as you don’t need to rebuild or drastically redesign anything.</li><li id="">Maintenance is much easier, since you’re using the same codebase for your site and your apps. When you update your site, your apps update automatically.</li><li id="">All the features on your website, such as plugins, themes, widgets, integrations, payment gateways and any custom features will work in the app in the same way.</li><li id="">There’s no coding, no technical knowledge needed from you or your team.</li><li id="">You can be totally hands-off and launch with zero addition to your existing workflow.</li></ul><p id="">Our full-service approach covers every part of the process. This includes:</p><ul id=""><li id="">Development work to convert your site into apps and deploy it for Android and iOS.</li><li id="">Configuring your app to ensure it feels fully native to the end user.</li><li id="">Custom UI/UX tweaks to your mobile website to maximize your mobile user experience in both app and website.</li><li id="">Submitting your app to the Apple and Google Play app stores, and handling all back-and-forths to ensure your app and listing meet their standards.</li><li id="">Handling technical updates and maintenance for your app after launching.</li></ul><p id="">The process starts with a <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id="">kick-off call</a> with one of our project managers. We’ll discuss your needs and what you want to get out of the project, and make sure MobiLoud is right for you.</p><p id="">From there, we take over to build and launch your apps, keeping you updated every step of the way.</p><p id="">From start to finish, you can be live and in the app stores in less than a month, for a low-four figure investment, plus a guarantee that your app will be accepted into the app stores, so it’s completely risk-free.</p><p id=""><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/pricing" id="">Learn more about our pricing here</a>.</p><p id="">Let’s take your eCommerce business to the next level by launching your own mobile apps. With MobiLoud, it’s easier than ever to get there.&nbsp;</p><p id="">Why wait? Your customers are already on mobile, and it’s time your business to jump on mobile too.</p><p id=""><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id="">Get in touch with us</a> to find out just how easy it is, and how much your business and brand can benefit from converting your BoldCommerce store to mobile apps.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <FAQSidebar faqs={faqs} />
